WEBVTT

00:00.820 --> 00:03.095
- THERE WAS A GUY
WHO WORKED FOR ME FOR TWO YEARS.

00:03.210 --> 00:04.586
HE NEVER SAID ANYTHING.

00:04.690 --> 00:05.850
I DIDN'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT HIS PERSONAL LIFE.

00:05.970 --> 00:06.959
I MISS THAT GUY.

00:07.070 --> 00:08.685
- I'M NOT THAT GUY.

00:08.800 --> 00:10.961
HE'S A VERY WEIRD,
GRUMPY GUY.

00:11.080 --> 00:12.001
WHO KNOWS IF IT WILL
EVEN WORK OUT?

00:12.110 --> 00:13.316
- I HAVE A DOCTOR APPOINTMENT,

00:13.420 --> 00:14.523
SO I'LL JUST
MEET YOU GUYS THERE.

00:14.630 --> 00:17.497
- KRISTINA BRAVERMAN?

00:29.850 --> 00:32.330
- ALL RIGHT, SO THEY SAID
THE VENDING MACHINE

00:32.440 --> 00:35.819
WAS IN THE HALL
NEAR THE WATER FOUNTAIN.

00:35.930 --> 00:37.409
- DORITOS, BABY.

00:37.520 --> 00:39.784
- NOW, SKI'I'I'LES COST 75 CENTS,
AND I'VE GOT $5,

00:39.900 --> 00:41.515
SO I'M DEFINITELY GETTING
TWO PACKETS OF THOSE,

00:41.620 --> 00:42.484
AND THEN SOMETHING ELSE.

00:42.590 --> 00:43.898
THIS IS GREAT.

00:44.000 --> 00:47.527
I CAN GET WHATEVER I WANT,
AND NO ONE CAN SAY NO TO ME.

00:47.630 --> 00:50.485
- WAIT, THIS IS WHERE
THE WATER FOUNTAIN IS.

00:50.600 --> 00:54.070
- WHERE'S THE VENDING MACHINE?
- THEY TOOK IT AWAY LAST JUNE.

00:56.220 --> 00:58.609
- NO.
- AW, MAN.

00:58.710 --> 01:01.531
- NO. NO, IT'S NOT FAIR!

01:01.640 --> 01:02.709
NO.

01:02.820 --> 01:04.606
IT'S NOT FAIR!

01:04.710 --> 01:07.599
HOW COULD THEY DO--

01:07.720 --> 01:10.848
[panﬁng]

01:10.960 --> 01:13.645
NO.
- MAN, CHILL OUT.

01:18.870 --> 01:21.384
- WELL, I AM SO GLAD
I'VE HAD THE CHANCE TO CHECK OUT

01:21.490 --> 01:25.381
THE 2007 DECEMBER ISSUE
OF WOMAN'S DAY.

01:25.490 --> 01:28.630
I FEEL LIKE I'VE REDISCOVERED
MY HOLIDAY SPIRIT.

01:28.740 --> 01:33.609
I NOW KNOW FIVE AMAZING WAYS
TO REUSE GIFT WRAP.

01:33.710 --> 01:34.847
WELL, IT'S OFFICIAL--

01:34.950 --> 01:36.815
OUR APPOINTMENT
WAS TWO HOURS AGO.

01:36.920 --> 01:38.262
- YEP.

01:38.370 --> 01:39.746
- CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT?
- YEAH, I KNOW.

01:39.850 --> 01:41.431
- I MEAN, WHAT KIND OF A WAY
IS THAT TO RUN A PRACTICE?

01:41.540 --> 01:44.122
- I DON'T KNOW, ADAM.
IT'S JUST THE WAY IT IS.

01:44.240 --> 01:45.502
- IT'S A CRAPPY WAY
TO RUN A PRACTICE.

01:45.620 --> 01:48.919
- IT'S CRAP, OKAY?
IT'S CRAP.

01:49.030 --> 01:51.169
- IT'S YOUR FIRST TIME, RIGHT?

01:51.280 --> 01:53.931
NEW KID ON THE CANCER BLOCK?

01:54.040 --> 01:56.315
YOUR HAIR'S
A DEAD GIVEAWAY.

01:56.420 --> 01:57.557
- OH.

01:57.660 --> 01:58.934
- PLUS THE HUSBANDS
STOP COMING AFTER A WHILE.

01:59.040 --> 02:00.689
- OH.
- I'M GWEN CHAMBERS.

02:00.810 --> 02:02.311
- HI, I'M KRISTINA.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

02:02.430 --> 02:05.285
- THIS IS MY HUSBAND ADAM.
- HI. HOW ARE YOU?

02:05.400 --> 02:06.389
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

02:06.500 --> 02:08.252
- SO WHAT STAGE?
[phone chimes]

02:08.360 --> 02:10.089
- I'M SORRY?
- WHAT STAGE?

02:10.190 --> 02:11.509
- OH, I DON'T KNOW.

02:11.610 --> 02:12.918
WE'RE JUST HERE
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

02:13.020 --> 02:15.477
- OH, I WAS 2B.
- I'M NOT ZB.

02:15.580 --> 02:16.956
- OH! THAT IS THE QUESTION.

02:17.060 --> 02:18.334
- [laughs] THAT'S FUNNY.

02:18.440 --> 02:20.829
- I HAD TO DO A LUMPECTOMY,
CHEMO, AND RADIATION.

02:20.930 --> 02:23.546
THE TRIPLE CROWN.
HELLO, MEDICAL MARIJUANA, HUH?

02:23.660 --> 02:24.581
- HM.
- WOW.

02:24.690 --> 02:26.897
- GWEN CHAMBERS?
- OH. ONE SEC, CARMEN.

02:27.000 --> 02:29.628
LISTEN, ALL THIS REALLY
MESSES WITH YOUR HEAD.

02:29.730 --> 02:31.379
YOU'RE GONNA GET REALLY
CONFUSED, REALLY FAST.

02:31.490 --> 02:33.697
CALL ME. SERIOUSLY.
- THAT'S NICE. OKAY.

02:33.800 --> 02:35.529
- DON'T WORRY, I WON'T TRY
TO GET YOU TO TAKE SHOTS

02:35.630 --> 02:36.870
OF WHEATGRASS.

02:36.980 --> 02:39.187
THAT CRAP MADE ME
MORE NAUSEOUS THAN THE CHEMO.

02:39.290 --> 02:40.632
- I'LL BET.

02:40.740 --> 02:43.459
- THANK YOU.
HAVE A GOOD VISIT.

02:44.850 --> 02:48.889
- I CAN'T IMAGINE WHY HER
HUSBAND STOPPED SHOWING UP.

02:50.370 --> 02:53.373
- [sighs] ADAM.

02:53.480 --> 02:55.198
- I KNOW YOU'VE PROBABLY
NEVER MET A PIRATE BEFORE.

02:55.310 --> 02:56.447
I'VE GOT CANCER JUST LIKE YOU.
- STOP.

02:56.550 --> 02:58.927
- WHAT?
- YOU'RE JUST ROTTEN.

02:59.040 --> 03:00.519
[laughter]

03:00.620 --> 03:02.315
- I KNOW THAT THIS
IS, LIKE, REALLY LAST MINUTE.

03:02.420 --> 03:03.899
- YEAH.
- BUT WE'RE DESPERATE.

03:04.010 --> 03:07.525
OUR WEDDING PHOTOGRAPHER,
WHO WE BOOKED A YEAR AGO--

03:07.630 --> 03:09.734
HELLO--HAS WEST NILE VIRUS.

03:09.840 --> 03:11.523
- [chuckles] OH, I--
SORRY, IT'S NOT FUNNY AT ALL.

03:11.630 --> 03:13.564
IT'S JUST YOU HEAR ABOUT IT.
- NO. I KNOW.

03:13.670 --> 03:14.898
- IT'S REAL.

03:15.020 --> 03:16.328
- AND OUR WEDDING
IS LESS THAN A WEEK AWAY, SO--

03:16.430 --> 03:18.705
- OH.
- BAD TIMING ON HER PART.

03:18.810 --> 03:21.051
- RIGHT. ACCORDING TO THE BOOKS,
WE'RE FREE, SO WE'LL--HANK!

03:21.160 --> 03:22.809
THIS IS DAN AND CARRIE.
- HELLO.

03:22.920 --> 03:25.480
- AND THEY'RE GETTING MARRIED ON
SATURDAY, AND THEY ARE LOOKING

03:25.580 --> 03:26.740
FOR A PHOTEIGMPHER...

03:26.860 --> 03:28.122
- FOR THEIR WEDDING.

03:28.240 --> 03:29.468
- I HEARD THAT YOU DID
JOURNALISTIC STYLE?

03:29.580 --> 03:30.956
- OH, UM--
- JOURNALISTIC?

03:31.070 --> 03:33.618
- YES. WELL, HE CAN DO
SO MANY DIFFERENT STYLES.

03:33.730 --> 03:35.413
HE'S SO TALENTED.

03:35.520 --> 03:37.932
AND, UM, SO WHAT KIND OF THINGS
WERE YOU LOOKING FOR?

03:38.040 --> 03:40.452
- WELL, WE REALLY WANT SOMETHING
THAT'S MORE KIND OF--

03:40.560 --> 03:41.766
- SLICE OF LIFE.
- YEAH, CANDID.

03:41.870 --> 03:43.451
SO, LIKE, PICTURES
OF ME GETTING READY

03:43.560 --> 03:45.073
BEFORE THE CEREMONY...
- OH!

03:45.190 --> 03:47.420
- AND THEN THE CEREMONY WHEN
WE, LIKE, RELEASE THE DOVES.

03:47.530 --> 03:49.395
- DOVES!
- YEAH.

03:49.500 --> 03:50.842
- HANK, DID YOU HEAR THAT?
- YEAH.

03:50.950 --> 03:52.429
- BIG WEDDING, HUH?

03:52.540 --> 03:53.916
- I'VE BEEN ON THE PALEO DIET
FOR, LIKE, EIGHT MONTHS.

03:54.020 --> 03:55.464
- I MEAN, OBVIOUSLY IT WORKS.
I JUST--YOU KNOW.

03:55.580 --> 03:56.842
- BABE, YOU LOOK AMAZING.

03:56.960 --> 03:58.120
- WELL, YOU BETTER BELIEVE
I WANT MY PICTURE TAKEN.

03:58.230 --> 03:59.572
- YEAH.

03:59.680 --> 04:01.477
- YOU KNOW, I'M ACTUALLY
BOOKED ON SATURDAY.

04:01.580 --> 04:02.854
- NO, WE'RE--SORRY, HE'S WRONG.
WE'RE FREE. WE'RE FREE.

04:02.960 --> 04:04.404
- NOPE.

04:04.520 --> 04:07.205
- SORRY. WHAT DO WE HAVE?
- IT'S NOT IN THE BOOK.

04:07.310 --> 04:10.370
I'M TAKING A PERSONAL DAY
ON SATURDAY.

04:10.490 --> 04:12.037
- CAN IT--CAN IT
BE ANOTHER DAY

04:12.140 --> 04:13.892
FOR YOUR PERSON?

04:14.010 --> 04:14.931
- IT'S A "ME" DAY.

04:15.040 --> 04:16.382
I CAN'T.
IT'S A--

04:16.490 --> 04:18.663
- IT'S A "ME" DAY?
- IT'S A "ME" DAY!

04:18.770 --> 04:22.069
IT'S FOR ME. THAT'S THE DAY
THAT ME WANTS IT, SO...

04:22.190 --> 04:23.396
HEY, LOOK, I'M SORRY.

04:23.500 --> 04:24.660
I CAN'T TAKE
YOUR WEDDING PHOTOS.

04:24.780 --> 04:25.804
- I'M SO SORRY.

04:25.920 --> 04:27.421
- EVEN IF WE WERE,
LIKE, TO PAY EXTRA?

04:27.540 --> 04:29.019
- BABY, LET'S GO, COME ON.
- I'M SO SORRY.

04:29.130 --> 04:30.506
- WE'RE REALLY DESPERATE.
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

04:30.610 --> 04:35.479
- IF IT CHANGES, PLEASE CALL ME.
- COME ON.

04:35.580 --> 04:37.923
[door slams]
- SERIOUSLY?

04:38.030 --> 04:42.137
- I DON'T DO WEDDINGS.

04:42.240 --> 04:45.300
I NEED HELP HERE.
- [SlghS]

04:45.420 --> 04:46.751
- SO, YEAH, THERE WAS
A VENDING MACHINE

04:46.870 --> 04:48.485
IN THE SCHOOL LAST YEAR,
BUT THEY TOOK IT OUT.

04:48.590 --> 04:51.036
- MAX, GIVE IT UP.
THEY TOOK THE VENDING MACHINE.

04:51.150 --> 04:52.526
- IT'S NOT FAIR.

04:52.630 --> 04:55.258
- YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO LEARN
LIFE IS NOT FAIR.

04:55.360 --> 04:58.113
OH, DAMN, CRAP, HELL!

04:58.220 --> 04:59.630
[kids giggling]

04:59.740 --> 05:01.628
- WHY ARE YOU BEING SO LOUD?
- WELL, THAT WAS OUR TURN.

05:01.740 --> 05:04.629
HEY, DON'T TELL YOUR PARENTS
I SAID ANY OF THAT, ALL RIGHT?

05:04.750 --> 05:06.809
[car tires squealing]
HOLD ON HERE, FELLAS.

05:06.920 --> 05:09.332
- WHOO!
- [chuckles]

05:12.070 --> 05:13.514
[siren chirps]

05:13.620 --> 05:16.407
- BUSTED!
- HUH?

05:16.520 --> 05:19.557
OH, CRAP.
DAMN IT.

05:19.660 --> 05:22.242
- YOU HAVE TO PULL OVER.
- YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I'M DOING

05:22.350 --> 05:24.386
IS PULLING OVER.
- OH.

05:24.490 --> 05:29.496
- OH, DAMN IT.

05:29.600 --> 05:31.830
- WHAT'S SO BAD ABOUT THIS?
- OH, HE'S A YOUNG GUY.

05:31.950 --> 05:33.702
- WHY IS THAT BAD?

05:33.810 --> 05:35.493
- IT'S BAD BECAUSE HE DOESN'T
HAVE ANY PATIENCE, I BET YOU.

05:35.610 --> 05:37.009
- LICENSE
AND REGISTRATION, PLEASE.

05:37.120 --> 05:41.079
- HI. YEAH, SO WHAT'S
THE PROBLEM HERE, OFFICER?

05:41.200 --> 05:42.815
- COULD I HAVE YOUR LICENSE
AND REGISTRATION, SIR?

05:42.920 --> 05:44.262
- YEAH, I'M GETTING IT.
- ARE WE IN TROUBLE?

05:44.370 --> 05:47.851
- NO, HONEY,
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

05:47.960 --> 05:51.544
THERE YOU GO.

05:51.660 --> 05:53.992
- SIR, ARE YOU AWARE THAT
YOUR DRIVER'S LICENSE EXPIRED

05:54.110 --> 05:55.065
MORE THAN A YEAR AGO?

05:55.180 --> 05:56.863
- ARE YOU SURE?

05:56.970 --> 05:58.551
[pen clicking]
OH, THAT'S A MISTAKE.

05:58.660 --> 05:59.900
HEY, LISTEN, OFFICER,
I'M WITH MY GRANDKIDS.

06:00.010 --> 06:01.591
I MEAN, YOU CAN SEE THAT.

06:01.700 --> 06:04.692
COULDN'T YOU JUST
GIVE ME A WARNING THIS TIME?

06:04.810 --> 06:06.425
HUH?

06:06.530 --> 06:08.942
WHAT, ARE YOU WRITING
THE TICKET ALREADY?

06:09.050 --> 06:12.224
HEY, UH, LET ME HANDLE THIS.
- SIR, GET BACK INSIDE YOUR CAR.

06:12.330 --> 06:13.809
- YEAH, NO--I JUST WANNA TALK
TO YOU,

06:13.920 --> 06:14.909
JUST FOR ONE SECOND.
- DO YOU HEAR ME, SIR?

06:15.020 --> 06:17.477
GET BACK INSIDE
YOUR CAR RIGHT NOW, SIR.

06:17.580 --> 06:19.263
- I DON'T THINK YOU HEARD ME!

06:19.370 --> 06:21.509
- WHA--OW! HEY! EASY!

06:21.620 --> 06:23.099
- GRANDPA! GRANDPA, PLEASE!
NO! NO! NO!

06:23.210 --> 06:24.962
- IT'S ALL RIGHT, KIDS!
JUST EAT YOUR ICE CREAM, KIDS!

06:25.070 --> 06:27.447
I'M STAYING STILL.
WHAT, I'M GONNA RUN?

06:27.550 --> 06:29.415
[handcuffs clicking]
DAMN.

06:29.520 --> 06:32.626
[Lucy Schwartz's
When We Were Young]

06:34.390 --> 06:37.109
- WHEN WE WERE YOUNG
WE WERE SMALL

06:37.220 --> 06:40.804
BUT WE DIDN'T
KNOW IT

06:40.910 --> 06:44.289
AH AHH AH

06:44.400 --> 06:47.221
WHEN YOU WERE HURT
YOU WOULD SMILE

06:47.330 --> 06:50.777
SO YOU DIDN'T
SHOW IT

06:50.890 --> 06:54.337
AH AHH AH

06:54.440 --> 06:58.228
AND I

06:58.340 --> 07:02.231
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

07:05.800 --> 07:08.655
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:10.800 --> 07:13.803
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:26.270 --> 07:30.195
- WHEN CAN WE GET HER IN?

07:30.310 --> 07:33.518
- WE HAVE...

07:34.520 --> 07:35.748
- GOOD. THAT WORKS.

07:35.860 --> 07:38.033
YOU CAN COVER UP NOW,
MRS. BRAVERMAN.

07:38.140 --> 07:42.213
MRS. BRAVERMAN, I UNDERSTAND
THAT YOUR ONCOLOGIST

07:42.320 --> 07:44.072
IS DR. GARDNER?

07:44.180 --> 07:48.071
- YEAH, UM, WE JUST MET HIM,
SO I MEAN, I GUESS HE IS.

07:48.190 --> 07:50.522
HE SAID THAT YOUR PRACTICE
WAS THE PLACE TO GO,

07:50.640 --> 07:51.777
AND IF HIS WIFE HAD CANCER,
HE'D SEND HER TO YOU.

07:51.880 --> 07:53.222
- MM-HMM.

07:53.330 --> 07:54.809
- HEY, LISTEN, DOCTOR,
IF THERE'S ANYTHING YOU COULD

07:54.920 --> 07:56.433
TELL US NOW, YOU KNOW,
WE'VE BEEN IN THE DARK.

07:56.540 --> 07:57.746
WE'VE BEEN WAITING OUTSIDE
FOR 2 1/2 HOURS.

07:57.850 --> 07:59.158
WE'D APPRE_CIATE IT.
[phone rings]

07:59.270 --> 08:00.749
WHAT?
- IT'S FINE.

08:00.850 --> 08:02.056
- I'M JUST TRYING TO FIND OUT--
- WE'RE HERE NOW.

08:02.170 --> 08:03.683
- YEAH. MM-HMM.
WELL, LET'S MAKE SURE

08:03.790 --> 08:04.814
WE GET ALL THE RESULTS
BACK FIRST

08:04.930 --> 08:06.067
BEFORE WE JUMP
TO CONCLUSIONS.

08:06.170 --> 08:09.344
I NEED THE RESULTS
ON THE BRACA ASAP.

08:09.450 --> 08:11.202
YEAH.
WELL, CALL THE GENETICIST

08:11.310 --> 08:12.277
AT CITY OF HOPE AND TELL HIM

08:12.380 --> 08:13.756
I NEED IT.

08:13.870 --> 08:15.076
- WHAT IS HE DOING?
- I DON'T KNOW.

08:15.180 --> 08:16.966
EXCUSE ME--
- ALL RIGHT, MRS. BRAVERMAN.

08:17.080 --> 08:19.969
YOUR CANCER IS 1.6 CENTIMETERS,
AND IS LOCATED

08:20.080 --> 08:22.310
IN THE LOWER OUTER QUADRANT
OF YOUR LEI-T BREAST,

08:22.430 --> 08:23.738
NEAR THE CHEST WALL.

08:23.840 --> 08:26.707
THERE'S NO EVIDENCE OF CANCER
ELSEWHERE IN THE BREAST.

08:26.810 --> 08:29.187
- OKAY, 1.6 CENTIMETERS.
THAT SEEMS--

08:29.300 --> 08:30.744
- IT'S A SMALL TUMOR.
- GOOD.

08:30.850 --> 08:32.260
- GOOD, SO SHE MAY NOT
NEED CHEMO.

08:32.370 --> 08:33.883
- WELL, WE DON'T KNOW YET.

08:33.990 --> 08:35.150
THE SIZE OF THE TUMOR IS JUST
ONE OF THE CHARACTERISTICS

08:35.270 --> 08:36.544
WE LOOK AT.

08:36.650 --> 08:37.992
A SMALL TUMOR
CAN BE VERY AGGRESSIVE.

08:38.100 --> 08:39.579
WE NEED TO KNOW MORE ABOUT
THE CHARACTER OF THE CANCER.

08:39.690 --> 08:40.918
THAT WILL AFFECT OUR TREATMENT.

08:41.030 --> 08:44.750
REGARDLESS, WE NEED
TO DO A LUMPECTOMY.

08:44.860 --> 08:46.999
- A LUMPECTOMY.
THAT MEANS WHAT?

08:47.110 --> 08:48.316
- WE SURGICALLY
REMOVE THE CANCER

08:48.420 --> 08:49.694
WHILE PRESERVING THE BREAST.

08:49.800 --> 08:52.769
- SO THERE'S SURGERY
INVOLVED RIGHT OFF THE BAT.

08:52.870 --> 08:54.280
- YOU'LL HAVE A SCAR.

08:54.390 --> 08:56.278
THERE WILL BE A SLIGHT
TO MODERATE DISFIGUREMENT.

08:56.390 --> 08:59.735
- YEAH. I DON'T CARE ABOUT
THE SCAR OR ANY OF THAT.

08:59.840 --> 09:01.182
IF THERE'S ANY--
- OKAY.

09:01.290 --> 09:02.427
- IF MY BREAST LOOKS WEIRD.
I DON'T CARE.

09:02.540 --> 09:04.360
I JUST WANT THE CANCER OUT,
YOU KNOW.

09:04.470 --> 09:05.949
- MRS. BRAVERMAN.
I'M REALLY VERY GOOD.

09:06.060 --> 09:07.709
I'LL GIVE YOU
A GOOD RESULT.

09:07.820 --> 09:10.505
NOW WHEN WE DO THE LUMPECTOMY,
WE WILL ALSO REMOVE

09:10.610 --> 09:13.022
TWO SENTINEL LYMPH NODES
FROM YOUR ARM PIT.

09:13.130 --> 09:14.097
WE'LL ANALYZE THE NODES,
AND THAT WILL TELL US

09:14.200 --> 09:16.088
WHETHER OR NOT
THE CANCER HAS SPREAD

09:16.210 --> 09:18.781
TO YOUR LYMPHATIC SYSTEM.

09:18.900 --> 09:20.515
- AND IF IT HAS SPREAD...

09:20.620 --> 09:21.962
- WELL, DEPENDING ON
THE LEVEL OF INVOLVEMENT,

09:22.070 --> 09:24.630
WE NEED TO CONSIDER
DOING ANOTHER PROCEDURE

09:24.730 --> 09:26.174
TO TAKE OUT MORE.

09:26.280 --> 09:29.113
IT WILL ALSO MEAN THAT
YOU'LL NEED CHEMOTHERAPY.

09:29.220 --> 09:31.313
- WAIT, IF IT SPREADS
TO THE LYMPHATIC SYSTEM--

09:31.430 --> 09:33.216
I MEAN, IS THERE ANOTHER WAY
OF DOING THIS, OTHER OPTIONS?

09:33.330 --> 09:34.706
OR IS THIS--

09:34.810 --> 09:35.970
- I JUST TOLD YOU
WHAT I THINK YOU NEED TO DO.

09:36.090 --> 09:37.318
- RIGHT.

09:37.430 --> 09:39.079
WELL, WE JUST FOUND OUT
ABOUT THIS, LIKE, LESS THAN

09:39.190 --> 09:40.634
A WEEK AGO.

09:40.750 --> 09:41.978
I MEAN, SO WE DON'T
KNOW WHAT WE'RE DOING.

09:42.090 --> 09:43.717
- MRS. BRAVERMAN,
A LUMPECTOMY PERFORMED

09:43.820 --> 09:46.095
SOONER RATHER THAN LATER,
OFFERS THE BEST CHANCE

09:46.200 --> 09:47.269
OF REMISSION.

09:47.370 --> 09:49.190
AND I HAVE AN OPENING
FRIDAY THE 26TH AT--

09:49.310 --> 09:52.825
- 8:00.
- 8:00 AM.

09:52.930 --> 09:55.171
[phone rings]
- OKAY.

09:55.280 --> 09:56.679
DOCTOR, I JUST--
- YEAH?

09:56.800 --> 09:59.200
NO! HE'S YOUR COUSIN.
- [sighs]

09:59.320 --> 10:01.288
- HE DOES NOT KNOW HOW
TO READ A PATHOLOGY REPORT.

10:01.390 --> 10:02.971
HE'S ALSO A VETERINARIAN.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.934
LET ME READ THE REPORT,
ALL RIGHT?

10:05.050 --> 10:06.494
LET HIM TAKE CARE
OF YOUR DOG.

10:06.600 --> 10:09.160
- I'M WORKING
FOR A CRAZY PERSON.

10:09.260 --> 10:10.602
WHAT AM I WASHING THESE?
- YES, PLEASE.

10:10.710 --> 10:12.041
- WITH SOAP?
- NO. JUST RINSE THEM.

10:12.160 --> 10:13.536
- I'M JUST KIDDING.
- [chuckles]

10:13.640 --> 10:14.914
- HE'S PRESENTED
WITH A HUGE PAYDAY.

10:15.020 --> 10:17.124
A WEDDING. WHICH SEEMS
A PERFECTLY NORMAL THING

10:17.230 --> 10:18.401
FOR A PHOTOGRAPHER TO DO.

10:18.510 --> 10:20.364
BUT NO.
HE DOESN'T DO WEDDINGS.

10:20.480 --> 10:23.233
LIKE THAT'S SOMEHOW BENEATH HIM.
HE MADE THE BRIDE CRY.

10:23.340 --> 10:25.376
- HE'S REALLY GETTING
UNDER YOUR SKIN, HUH?

10:25.480 --> 10:28.062
- WELL, HE'S REALLY INSULTING
AND DIFFICULT TO WORK FOR.

10:28.170 --> 10:30.058
- YOU SHOULD
CONVINCE HIM TO DO IT.

10:30.180 --> 10:31.556
- I CAN'T IMAGINE
HOW I WOULD DO THAT.

10:31.660 --> 10:33.036
- HERE, LOOK.

10:33.140 --> 10:34.459
[imitating Hank]
I DON'T WANT TO DO A WEDDING.

10:34.560 --> 10:36.073
- WAIT, THAT'S HIM?

10:36.180 --> 10:37.863
- YEAH. I'M BEING HIM.
- OKAY, MUCH LESS CHARMING.

10:37.980 --> 10:39.902
YOU HAVE TO BE MUCH MORE ANGRY,
AND YOU DON'T LIKE WOMEN.

10:40.010 --> 10:41.113
- [imitating Hank]
I DON'T LIKE TO DO WEDDINGS.

10:41.220 --> 10:42.664
- NICE.
- I DON'T LIKE ANYTHING.

10:42.780 --> 10:44.259
- BUT, HANK,
YOU SHOULD DO WEDDINGS.

10:44.360 --> 10:47.602
YOU'D MAKE SO MUCH MONEY.
- I DON'T LIKE MONEY.

10:47.710 --> 10:49.359
I DON'T BELIEVE IN IT.
I DON'T KNOW.

10:49.470 --> 10:50.698
- CLOSE ENOUGH.
- OKAY.

10:50.820 --> 10:53.857
- OKAY, BUT I AM AN ASSISTANT,
AND I COULD USE

10:53.960 --> 10:55.575
SOME VALUABLE EXPERIENCE.

10:55.680 --> 10:58.137
- BUT I DON'T CARE ABOUT YOU.
- THAT'S TRUE.

10:58.240 --> 10:59.400
- [chuckles]

10:59.520 --> 11:00.919
- WELL, YOU KNOW,
YOU WERE RUDE TO THESE PEOPLE

11:01.030 --> 11:02.657
AND TH EY'LL GO
TELL THEIR FRIENDS,

11:02.760 --> 11:04.136
AND THAT'S REALLY BAD
FOR BUSINESS, AND YOU'RE

11:04.240 --> 11:05.446
INCREDIBLY PATRONIZING
WHEN YOU TALK TO EVERYONE,

11:05.560 --> 11:08.859
ESPECIALLY ME.

11:08.970 --> 11:11.837
I THINK I'VE REALIZED
WHAT BOTHERS ME THE MOST.

11:11.940 --> 11:12.736
YOU'RE INSULTING
AND PATRONIZING TO ME.

11:12.840 --> 11:16.833
I WISH YOU WOULD BE NICER.

11:16.950 --> 11:19.464
- AND HANK'S HEART
GREW TWO SIZES THAT DAY.

11:19.570 --> 11:20.605
- IT DID?
- [laughs] I THINK SO.

11:20.710 --> 11:21.984
- DID I GET YOU?

11:22.090 --> 11:23.250
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE
VERY REASONABLE, YEAH.

11:23.370 --> 11:24.849
- OKAY.

11:24.960 --> 11:26.291
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND, HE WAS--
- WAIT, WAS HE SPEEDING?

11:26.400 --> 11:27.810
WAS HE DRIVING REALLY FAST?
- HE WAS AWESOME.

11:27.920 --> 11:29.296
- IT WAS RIDING IN THE BACK
OF A POLICE CAR.

11:29.410 --> 11:30.991
- GREAT. BACK OF A POLICE CAR.
- THAT IS EXCITING.

11:31.100 --> 11:32.852
- IT WAS KIND OF
A COOL ADVENTURE, REALLY.

11:32.960 --> 11:34.268
THAT HE WAS ON.

11:34.380 --> 11:35.779
- PLEASE DON'T ACT
LIKE THIS IS NOTHING.

11:35.900 --> 11:37.379
- I'M JUST TRYING TO--
- THIS IS SILLY.

11:37.480 --> 11:38.754
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S GOING ON RIGHT NOW.

11:38.870 --> 11:40.826
- THERE HE IS.
DAD! WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

11:40.940 --> 11:42.931
- SOME OVERZEALOUS COP
IS TRYING TO FILL

11:43.040 --> 11:44.621
HIS WEEKLY QUOTA
OF TICKETS.

11:44.730 --> 11:46.049
THAT'S WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED.

11:46.150 --> 11:48.459
- OKAY, ZEEK, LET'S TRY
AND KEEP CALM, OKAY?

11:48.560 --> 11:49.492
- THEY GOT NO OVERSIGHT
AND NO ACCOUNTABILITY

11:49.600 --> 11:51.397
IN THIS PLACE.

11:51.500 --> 11:52.467
- DAD!
- I OUGHT TO SUE!

11:52.570 --> 11:54.083
- HEY, WHOA.
JEEZ!

11:54.190 --> 11:55.418
- LET'S GET OUTTA HERE
BEFORE THEY ARREST HIM AGAIN.

11:55.540 --> 11:56.461
- HOW COULD THEY
ARREST HIM AGAIN?

11:56.570 --> 11:57.878
HE HASN'T BROKEN ANY LAWS.

11:57.990 --> 11:59.218
- I'M SAYING I THINK
HE MADE A BAD CALL.

11:59.330 --> 12:00.774
I REALLY DON'T
APPRECIATE THE FACT

12:00.890 --> 12:01.959
THAT HE WAS YELLING
IN FRONT OF THE KIDS.

12:02.060 --> 12:03.436
- RIGHT.

12:03.550 --> 12:05.097
- BUT HE'S GONNA RETAKE
HIS DRIVER'S TEST, PAY HIS FINE.

12:05.200 --> 12:06.474
END OF STORY.

12:06.580 --> 12:07.649
- YEAH, WELL HOPEFULLY
THAT'S THE END OF THE STORY.

12:07.760 --> 12:08.852
BUT MAYBE NOT.

12:08.960 --> 12:10.587
MAYBE THERE'S
A REASON WHY

12:10.690 --> 12:12.339
HE'S LET HIS LICENSE
EXPIRE BY A YEAR.

12:12.450 --> 12:14.759
- I'M JUST PRAYING HE'S NOT
DELINQUENT ON HIS SMOG TEST.

12:14.870 --> 12:17.316
- I KNOW. GOD.
- SHOULD HE BE DRIVING?

12:17.420 --> 12:18.580
- JULIA, COME ON.
- I THINK HE'S FINE.

12:18.700 --> 12:21.589
- JUST ONE POORLY TIMED U-TURN,
I THINK.

12:21.700 --> 12:23.691
- I THINK HE'S FINE.
- HE'S DRIVING OUR KIDS AROUND.

12:23.810 --> 12:25.357
MAKING ILLEGAL U-TU RNS.

12:25.460 --> 12:26.734
- I'D BE MORE WORRIED ABOUT
AMBER DRIVING YOUR KIDS AROUND.

12:26.840 --> 12:28.114
- AND HE IS
ON HEART MEDICATION.

12:28.230 --> 12:29.458
I DON'T KNOW
IF THAT'S IMPAIRING...

12:29.570 --> 12:30.980
- WITH HIS WHAT NOW?
- WHAT?

12:31.090 --> 12:32.944
- MOTOR CONTROL OR SOMETHING.
- WHAT HEART MEDICATION?

12:33.060 --> 12:34.504
- HE'S NOT ON HEART MEDICATION.
- IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

12:34.610 --> 12:37.226
HE JUST HAD A REALLY SMALL
HEART EPISODE LAST YEAR.

12:37.340 --> 12:39.092
- HE HAD A HEART ATTACK?
- DAD HAD A HEART ATTACK?

12:39.200 --> 12:41.259
[everyone talking at once]

12:41.380 --> 12:42.301
- OKAY. WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

12:42.410 --> 12:44.093
HE DID NOT HAVE
A HEART ATTACK, OKAY?

12:44.210 --> 12:47.099
HE HAD SOME FLUTTERING,
HE'S NOW ON MEDICINE THAT IS--

12:47.210 --> 12:48.791
- HOW DID YOU NOT TELL US THIS
ABOUT THE FLUTTERING?

12:48.900 --> 12:50.720
- I DON'T--BECAUSE
HE ASKED ME NOT TO--

12:50.830 --> 12:52.343
- SO HE IS ON SOMETHING.

12:52.460 --> 12:53.973
- THAT'S NOT WHAT
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT, OKAY?

12:54.080 --> 12:55.968
THIS IS ABOUT DAD
DRIVING WITHOUT A LICENSE.

12:56.080 --> 12:58.184
I'M ONLY SUGGESTING MAYBE THIS
VERY MILD MEDICATION HE'S ON

12:58.290 --> 13:00.076
COULD BE IMPAIRING HIS DRIVING.

13:00.190 --> 13:02.841
- WELL, MAYBE HE NEEDS TO NOT
BE DRIVING ON THE MEDICATION.

13:02.950 --> 13:04.349
THIS IS ENTIRELY RELEVANT.
[cell phone beeps]

13:04.470 --> 13:06.609
- BUT AGAIN, DON'T YOU THINK
HE WOULD KNOW

13:06.710 --> 13:08.018
IF HE NEEDS
TO BE NOT DRIVING?

13:08.130 --> 13:08.539
- WELL, MAYBE THAT'S WHY
HE'S NOT TAKING THE TEST AGAIN.

13:08.640 --> 13:10.813
THAT'S MY POINT.

13:10.920 --> 13:12.399
- BUT HE WOULDN'T
PUT THE KIDS IN THE CAR

13:12.510 --> 13:13.579
IF HE'S ON SOME MEDICATION
THAT'S MAKING HIM DROWSY

13:13.680 --> 13:14.612
OR WHATEVER.

13:14.720 --> 13:15.812
- I WOULD HOPE NOT,

13:15.930 --> 13:17.238
BUT, ADAM, WOULD YOU
LET HIM DRIVE NORA?

13:17.340 --> 13:19.581
- UH, I DON'T KNOW.
I GOTTA GO.

13:19.690 --> 13:22.727
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

13:22.830 --> 13:24.309
- WHAT?
- ALL RIGHT.

13:24.420 --> 13:26.695
- SO MAX WAS CALLING IT
A LOW-SPEED CHASE,

13:26.800 --> 13:28.859
WHICH I THINK PROBABLY
OFFENDED YOUR DAD,

13:28.980 --> 13:32.598
BUT IT WAS REALLY HILARIOUS.

13:32.700 --> 13:34.736
- HEY, KRISTINA.
CAN I SAY SOMETHING?

13:34.840 --> 13:37.729
- YES.

13:37.850 --> 13:41.468
- I REALLY DIDN'T
LIKE THAT DOCTOR.

13:41.570 --> 13:43.014
- OKAY.

13:43.130 --> 13:44.438
- I DIDN'T LIKE THE WAY
THAT HE MADE YOU WAIT.

13:44.540 --> 13:46.292
I DIDN'T LIKE THE WAY
HE ANSWERED HIS PHONE

13:46.410 --> 13:48.617
EVERY TIME IT RANG WHEN HE WAS
SUPPOSED TO BE FOCUSED ON YOU.

13:48.720 --> 13:51.166
I FEEL LIKE HE'S DISTRACTED.

13:51.270 --> 13:53.067
AND I WANT SOMEBODY
WHO'S GOING TO BE SENSITIVE

13:53.170 --> 13:54.307
TO WHAT YOU'RE GOING THROUGH.

13:54.410 --> 13:55.968
OBVIOUSLY, HONEY,
IT'S YOUR CALL.

13:56.070 --> 13:57.583
BUT I JUST FEEL LIKE
WE SHOULD FIND THE RIGHT PERSON.

13:57.690 --> 13:59.066
THE PERSON WHO'S GOING TO NIP
THIS THING IN THE BUD

13:59.180 --> 14:00.761
AND TAKE CARE OF YOU.

14:00.870 --> 14:01.939
- I KNOW, BUT HONEY HE ALSO SAID
THAT WE SHOULDN'T WAIT, SO...

14:02.040 --> 14:03.723
- I KNOW AND I AGREE.

14:03.840 --> 14:04.909
WE SHOULD MAKE AN APPOINTMENT
FOR SURGERY SO THAT WE DON'T

14:05.010 --> 14:06.284
LOSE THE DATE.

14:06.390 --> 14:07.493
BUT WE SHOULD
GET ANOTHER OPINION QUICKLY.

14:07.600 --> 14:09.704
- OKAY. THAT'S FINE.

14:09.810 --> 14:11.038
THAT'S FINE.
- OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

14:11.160 --> 14:12.878
HONEY, JUST TRYING
TO DO THE RIGHT THING HERE.

14:12.990 --> 14:14.799
- I KNOW. I KNOW.
- YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

14:14.920 --> 14:18.048
- HEY.
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

14:32.140 --> 14:34.347
[door opens]

14:36.970 --> 14:38.176
- UNBELIEVABLE.
- HEY.

14:38.290 --> 14:39.621
- HEY.
- I HAVE SOME CALLS FOR YOU.

14:39.740 --> 14:41.901
HERE.
- THANKS.

14:42.010 --> 14:43.420
- OH. UH, I JUST HEARD
THAT THE BAND

14:43.530 --> 14:45.157
THAT WE MISSED
THE MEETING FOR THE OTHER DAY

14:45.260 --> 14:48.320
UH, THEY JUST BOOKED
AT WEST END, SO...

14:48.430 --> 14:50.705
- SO WE JUST LOST THEM.
- UH, YEAH.

14:50.820 --> 14:53.368
- NOBODY COVERED FOR ME,
AND WE JUST LOST THEM. GREAT.

14:53.470 --> 14:55.119
- YEAH. WELL, I--YOU
WEREN'T ANSWERING YOUR PHONE,

14:55.230 --> 14:56.982
AND CROSBY WAS
IN A RECORDING SESSION

14:57.100 --> 14:57.998
SO, YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T--

14:58.100 --> 14:59.328
- WELL, YOU SHOULD HAVE JUST

14:59.450 --> 15:00.576
PULLED CROSBY OUT
OF THE SESSION, AMBER.

15:00.690 --> 15:02.305
- WELL, I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

15:02.410 --> 15:04.162
I MEAN, YOU SPECIFICALLY TOLD ME
I'M NEVER TO GO INTO A SESSION.

15:04.280 --> 15:05.895
- OKAY, WELL NOW I'M TELLING YOU
THAT IF SOMEBODY WANTS TO

15:06.000 --> 15:09.003
BOOK OUR STUDIO FOR FOUR WEEKS,
THAT YOU GO AND YOU GET CROSBY

15:09.110 --> 15:10.418
OUT OF THE SESSION, OKAY?

15:10.530 --> 15:12.213
WE LOST $10,000.

15:12.320 --> 15:13.662
- OKAY, I...

15:13.770 --> 15:16.250
- WHY DOES IT SMELL
LIKE BURNT COFFEE IN HERE?

15:16.360 --> 15:18.009
- BECAUSE I BURNED
SOME EARLIER--

15:18.120 --> 15:19.633
- ALL RIGHT, WELL
CAN YOU DEAL WITH THAT?

15:19.740 --> 15:23.085
AND CAN YOU PLEASE FIND A PLACE
TO PUT ALL THESE MAGAZINES

15:23.190 --> 15:24.600
THAT ARE LYING
ALL OVER THE PLACE?

15:24.710 --> 15:27.270
STACK THEM UP SO IT DOESN'T
LOOK LIKE COYOTES

15:27.370 --> 15:29.713
HAVE BEEN SCAVENGING
THROUGH A DOCTOR'S OFFICE?

15:29.820 --> 15:33.881
CROSBY!

15:34.000 --> 15:35.683
- COULD YOU BELIEVE JOHN?

15:35.790 --> 15:36.779
HE WAS JUST MOUTHING OFF
IN FRONT OF THE ENTIRE CLASS

15:36.900 --> 15:37.821
TO OUR TEACHER.

15:37.930 --> 15:40.137
IT WAS JUST CRAZY.

15:40.240 --> 15:41.036
- DID YOU KNOW THERE USED
TO BE A VENDING MACHINE

15:41.140 --> 15:42.277
BY THE WATER FOUNTAIN?

15:42.380 --> 15:44.268
- YEAH. THERE
WAS ONE LAST YEAR.

15:44.390 --> 15:45.869
- OKAY, SO YOU USED
TO BE ABLE TO BUY CANDY

15:45.970 --> 15:46.868
ANYTIME YOU WANTED.

15:46.980 --> 15:48.208
NOT DURING CLASS, OBVIOUSLY,

15:48.320 --> 15:49.969
BUT RECESS, BEFORE SCHOOL,
AFTER SCHOOL.

15:50.080 --> 15:52.014
YOU CAN'T DO THAT NOW.
THOSE DAYS ARE GONE.

15:52.120 --> 15:53.769
- MAX, LET'S GO.

15:53.880 --> 15:55.529
- IT SEEMS UNFAIR
THAT THERE ARE HUNDREDS,

15:55.640 --> 15:57.983
PROBABLY THOUSANDS OF KIDS
WHO GOT TO HAVE SKITTLES

15:58.090 --> 15:59.398
ANYTIME THEY WANTED.

15:59.510 --> 16:01.057
WE'RE NEW STUDENTS
COMING INTO THE SCHOOL

16:01.160 --> 16:02.195
AND WE DON'T HAVE THAT.

16:02.300 --> 16:03.676
IT'S OBVIOUSLY UNFAIR.

16:03.790 --> 16:05.951
- RIGHT.
GOOD LUCK WITH THAT.

16:06.060 --> 16:07.266
- IT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH LUCK.

16:07.380 --> 16:09.712
WE NEED TO FIND A WAY
TO GET THE SCHOOL

16:09.830 --> 16:13.209
TO BRING BACK
THE VENDING MACHINE!

16:13.310 --> 16:14.720
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

16:14.830 --> 16:18.516
- SO BEFORE WE START,
WOULD YOU LIKE WATER? TEA?

16:18.630 --> 16:20.245
ANYTHING?

16:20.350 --> 16:22.693
- UH, WOW. UM, NO.
- I'LL HAVE A BEER.

16:22.800 --> 16:24.040
JUST KIDDING.
- [laughs]

16:24.150 --> 16:26.801
- NOTHING FOR ME. THANKS.
- I'M JUST NERVOUS. SORRY.

16:26.910 --> 16:28.286
- IT'S OKAY.
NO, THANK YOU.

16:28.400 --> 16:31.039
- SO I FAMILIARIZED MYSELF

16:31.160 --> 16:34.368
WITH YOUR TESTS AND
MEDICAL RECORDS THIS MORNING.

16:34.470 --> 16:35.880
- RIGHT.

16:35.990 --> 16:39.198
- HOW ARE YOU DOING?

16:39.300 --> 16:42.781
- I MEAN, IT'S OVERWHELMING,
BUT I FIGURE A LOT OF WOMEN

16:42.890 --> 16:45.029
DEAL WITH IT, SO IT'S FINE.

16:45.140 --> 16:47.199
LIKE, IT'S--
- AND SO MANY WOMEN DO.

16:47.310 --> 16:49.722
BUT I'M HERE TO MAKE IT
LESS OVERWHELMING FOR YOU.

16:49.830 --> 16:51.479
- THANK YOU.

16:51.590 --> 16:54.900
- LET'S DISCUSS
THE BEST COURSE OF ACTION.

16:55.010 --> 16:58.935
I BELIEVE A LUMPECTOMY WOULD
BE THE RIGHT COURSE OF ACTION,

16:59.050 --> 17:00.312
BUT IT'S NOT
THE ONLY WAY TO GO.

17:00.430 --> 17:03.843
THE RESEARCH SHOWS
THAT WITH SURGERY,

17:03.950 --> 17:05.770
FOLLOWED BY RADIATION,

17:05.880 --> 17:09.816
OUR CHANCE OF CURE
IS THE SAME AS THE MASTECTOMY.

17:09.920 --> 17:11.080
- OKAY.

17:11.200 --> 17:14.954
- LOOK, I SEE YOU RECOVERING.

17:15.060 --> 17:17.028
YOU'RE GONNA
COME BACK FROM THIS.

17:17.130 --> 17:18.859
IT'S GONNA
BE A TOUGH YEAR...

17:18.960 --> 17:25.069
BUT YOU'RE GONNA MAKE IT.

17:25.180 --> 17:28.411
- THANK YOU.

17:31.180 --> 17:32.454
- [sighs] HEY.

17:32.560 --> 17:34.869
I WAS WONDERING
IF I COULD TALK TO YOU.

17:34.980 --> 17:36.493
- OH, THAT CAN'T BE GOOD.

17:36.600 --> 17:38.249
- LISTEN, IT'S NONE
OF MY BUSINESS IF YOU WANT

17:38.360 --> 17:40.533
TO TANK YOUR BUSINESS,
BUT IF YOU COULD POSSIBLY

17:40.640 --> 17:43.882
SPEAK MORE RESPECT FULLY
TO ME, THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

17:43.990 --> 17:45.298
- WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

17:45.400 --> 17:47.049
- SORRY.
IT'S JUST A SMALL THING.

17:47.160 --> 17:48.673
IT'S JUST--I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'RE AWARE OF--

17:48.790 --> 17:50.951
I'M JUST TALKING ABOUT
HOW YOU TALK TO ME.

17:51.070 --> 17:52.162
- YEAH. NO, I MEAN--
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,

17:52.270 --> 17:53.828
"TANKING MY BUSINESS"?

17:53.930 --> 17:56.990
- WELL, I MEAN, YOU KNOW.
JUST TURNING EVERYTHING DOWN.

17:57.110 --> 17:58.486
[chuckles]

17:58.590 --> 18:00.626
- THIS IS ABOUT
THE WEDDING THING AGAIN, RIGHT?

18:00.730 --> 18:02.209
- FOR EXAMPLE, YEAH.
IT IS ABOUT THE WEDDING.

18:02.320 --> 18:03.719
- I DON'T DO WEDDINGS.
JUST ON PRINCIPLE.

18:03.840 --> 18:05.660
- OKAY. IT'S A PRINCIPLE
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

18:05.770 --> 18:10.116
- LOOK, WEDDINGS ARE HASSLES.
IT'S MOTHERS AND BRIDESMAIDS.

18:10.220 --> 18:11.972
AND EVERYBODY'S DRUNK,
AND IF I HAVE TO SEE

18:12.090 --> 18:15.116
ANOTHER CHICKEN DANCE,
I'M GONNA KILL EVERYBODY, OKAY?

18:15.230 --> 18:17.460
IT'S DOVES CRAPPING ALL OVER
THE PLACE, IT'S JUST--

18:17.570 --> 18:18.741
IT'S HORRIBLE.

18:18.850 --> 18:20.431
- THAT'S THE CRAZIEST THING
I'VE EVER HEARD.

18:20.540 --> 18:21.848
A WEDDING IS SUPPOSED
TO BE THE MOST BEAUTIFUL DAY

18:21.960 --> 18:23.473
IN A COUPLE'S LIFE.

18:23.580 --> 18:25.059
I THINK IT'S JUST YOUR ATTITUDE.
- THAT IS MY ATTITUDE!

18:25.170 --> 18:26.125
- RIGHT.
- WEDDINGS SUCK.

18:26.240 --> 18:27.719
SO I DON'T DO THEM.

18:27.830 --> 18:29.058
- I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU SEEM TO TAKE PRIDE

18:29.170 --> 18:30.899
IN PUSHING PEOPLE AWAY.

18:31.000 --> 18:32.274
AND BUSINESS.

18:32.380 --> 18:33.824
- LOOK, I DON'T
HAVE TO TAKE EVERY JOB.

18:33.940 --> 18:35.202
- YOU DON'T TAKE ANY JOB!
- YOU DON'T TAKE ANY JOB.

18:35.320 --> 18:36.969
- WE'VE GOT A DATE BOOK
FULL OF EMPTY PAGES.

18:37.080 --> 18:41.141
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK?
I THINK YOU ARE A TRUE ARTIST,

18:41.250 --> 18:42.877
BUT YOU'RE AFRAID
THAT IF YOU'RE AN ARTIST

18:42.980 --> 18:44.766
WHO'S ALSO A GUY
WHO SHOOTS WEDDINGS,

18:44.880 --> 18:48.600
THEN SOMEHOW
YOU'RE A FAILURE.

18:48.710 --> 18:51.178
- THAT'S WHAT YOU THINK
THAT I THINK I AM?

18:51.300 --> 18:52.324
A FAILURE?

18:52.440 --> 18:54.886
- NO, NO, NO, NO.
I, UH...

18:54.990 --> 18:57.811
- 'CAUSE THAT WOULD MAKE YOU
A FAILURE'S ASSISTANT.

18:57.920 --> 18:59.569
- OKAY.

18:59.690 --> 19:03.069
LOOK, YOU KNOW, MY ONLY POINT
WAS I THINK YOU SHOULD HAVE

19:03.170 --> 19:04.341
DONE THE WEDDING.

19:04.450 --> 19:07.066
- I THOUGHT YOUR POINT
WAS HOW I TALKED TO YOU.

19:07.180 --> 19:09.512
- [sighs] THAT TOO.

19:09.630 --> 19:12.383
- OH, I CAN GUESS
WHAT THIS IS ALL ABOUT.

19:12.490 --> 19:13.627
- OH.

19:13.730 --> 19:15.209
- ONE OF MY GRANDKIDS
RATTED ME OUT, RIGHT?

19:15.320 --> 19:16.218
- WELL--
- NO.

19:16.320 --> 19:17.594
- NO, WHAT?

19:17.700 --> 19:19.349
- I WAS UNLAWFULLY
DETAINED BY THE WAY.

19:19.460 --> 19:21.041
- I'M PRETTY SURE IT WAS LEGAL
TO PULL YOU OVER.

19:21.160 --> 19:22.843
- ARRESTED FOR MAKING
AN ILLEGAL U-TURN.

19:22.950 --> 19:24.178
- YEAH.

19:24.300 --> 19:25.187
- THEN YOU GOT
LIPPY WITH THE COP.

19:25.300 --> 19:26.699
- LIPPY?
YEAH, LIPPY.

19:26.820 --> 19:28.742
WELL, I MAY HAVE USED
