'CAUSE YOU'RE GONNA NEED HIM.

31:30.640 --> 31:32.016
- YEAH, I AM GONNA NEED HIM.

31:32.130 --> 31:35.577
- HAVE YOU SCHEDULED
YOUR SURGERY YET?

31:35.680 --> 31:37.545
- NO, NOT YET.
I'M JUST--

31:37.650 --> 31:38.639
- WHAT ARE YOU
WAITING FOR?

31:38.750 --> 31:40.809
- I DIDN'T REALLY LIKE
DR. BEDSLOE.

31:40.930 --> 31:42.090
I THOUGHT HE WAS KIND OF--
- REALLY?

31:42.210 --> 31:44.849
- YEAH, KIND OF RUDE, AND--

31:44.970 --> 31:47.109
- HE SAVED MY LIFE.

31:47.210 --> 31:49.007
- WHAT DIDN'T YOU
LIKE ABOUT HIM?

31:49.110 --> 31:50.452
- WHEN WE WERE THERE
FOR MY APPOINTMENT,

31:50.560 --> 31:53.028
HE TOOK TWO PHONE CALLS
WITHIN, LIKE, FIVE MINUTES

31:53.150 --> 31:54.731
OF US BEING THERE.
IT WAS JUST DISMISSIVE--

31:54.840 --> 31:56.694
- YOU KNOW
WHO HE'S TALKING TO?

31:56.810 --> 31:58.528
HIS PATIENTS.

31:58.640 --> 32:00.187
I MEAN, HE GIVES YOU
HIS CELL PHONE NUMBER,

32:00.290 --> 32:02.178
AND HE ANSWERS IT EVERY TIME.

32:02.290 --> 32:04.087
HONEY, LISTEN,
YOU DON'T NEED A FRIEND.

32:04.190 --> 32:05.464
YOU NEED A DOCTOR.
HE'S NOT THERE

32:05.570 --> 32:07.458
TO MAKE YOU HAPPY.
HE'S THERE TO CURE YOU.

32:07.580 --> 32:09.400
I MUST'VE CALLED HIM
A THOUSAND TIMES

32:09.510 --> 32:10.954
THE THREE DAYS
BEFORE MY SURGERY.

32:11.060 --> 32:12.573
HE ANSWERED THE PHONE
EVERY TIME.

32:12.680 --> 32:13.999
HE NEVER ONCE SCREENED MY CALLS.

32:14.100 --> 32:16.853
- YEAH, I JUST FEEL
LIKE I NEED MORE INFORMATION.

32:16.960 --> 32:18.302
LIKE, MAYBE THERE'S
A BETTER DOCTOR, OR--

32:18.410 --> 32:21.038
- I REALLY THINK
YOU HAVE ALL THE INFORMATION

32:21.140 --> 32:23.108
THAT YOU NEED.
YOU REALLY DO.

32:23.210 --> 32:27.419
I THINK YOU NEED
TO GET IT THE HELL OUT, OKAY?

32:27.530 --> 32:29.521
DON'T WASTE TIME.

32:32.050 --> 32:35.019
- AND I, UH...

32:35.120 --> 32:37.600
I ALSO FEEL LIKE
I'M KINDA SCARED, YOU KNOW?

32:37.710 --> 32:39.496
- OF COURSE.

32:39.610 --> 32:42.989
- I FEEL LIKE I CAN TALK TO YOU.
I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOU.

32:43.090 --> 32:46.787
IT'S LIKE YOU'RE A STRANGER,
BUT I CAN'T REALLY--

32:46.890 --> 32:50.098
I CAN'T REALLY TALK
TO MY HUSBAND.

32:50.200 --> 32:52.168
- YEAH, WHY DO YOU FEEL
LIKE YOU CAN'T TALK TO HIM?

32:52.280 --> 32:54.896
- BECAUSE HE IS SO POSITIVE.

32:55.000 --> 32:57.309
HE'S LIKE THIS RELENTLESSLY
POSITIVE PERSON

32:57.420 --> 33:01.038
WHO CAN FIX EVERYTHING
AND MAKE EVERYTHING BETTER,

33:01.150 --> 33:04.119
AND IT'S LIKE--
- THAT'S--THAT IS A GOOD MAN

33:04.220 --> 33:05.903
WHO WANTS TO PROTECT YOU
FROM ANYTHING BAD HAPPENING,

33:06.010 --> 33:08.490
AND HERE'S THE THING.

33:08.600 --> 33:11.706
THE BAD THING
IS ALREADY HAPPENING.

33:13.750 --> 33:16.958
- RIGHT.

33:17.060 --> 33:20.166
[knocks on glass]

33:22.860 --> 33:24.191
- HI.
- YEAH, HI.

33:24.310 --> 33:26.642
- CAN YOU GET READY
IN LIKE, UH, FIVE MINUTES?

33:26.760 --> 33:27.988
- FOR WHAT?

33:28.100 --> 33:29.829
- LOCATION SHOOT.

33:29.930 --> 33:31.374
FOR THE WEDDING THING.

33:31.490 --> 33:33.481
IT'S AT
THE HILLCREST COUNTRY CLUB.

33:33.590 --> 33:35.933
- THE--THE WEDDING?

33:36.040 --> 33:38.099
- YEAH, CAN YOU GET READY?

33:38.220 --> 33:41.667
- [exhales, stutters]

33:41.770 --> 33:43.772
OKAY.

33:43.880 --> 33:47.600
YOU DON'T HAVE ANYTHING ELSE
YOU'D LIKE TO SAY TO ME?

33:47.710 --> 33:49.325
- BRING A SWEATER OR SOMETHING.
IT'S GONNA RUN LATE--

33:49.440 --> 33:51.123
- GREAT, OH--THAT'S
WHAT I WANTED, UH-HUH, OKAY.

33:51.230 --> 33:53.050
- IT'S INSIDE, BUT--
- SERIOUSLY--

33:53.160 --> 33:55.025
- HEY, HEY.

33:55.130 --> 33:57.018
- YEAH?
- YOU GOT ANYTHING TO EAT,

33:57.130 --> 33:58.336
'CAUSE I'M STARVING--
- OH, MY GOD.

33:58.450 --> 34:00.099
- YOU GOT A GRANOLA BAR
OR SOMETHIN'?

34:00.210 --> 34:01.302
- NO, I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING--
- I JUST FEEL LIKE--

34:01.410 --> 34:03.105
- THERE'S NO FULL KITCHEN
IN HERE.

34:03.210 --> 34:04.416
- ISN'T A FIG NEWTON
LAYING AROUND OR SOMETHIN'?

34:04.520 --> 34:05.964
- I HAVE TIME
TO MAKE YOU A SNACK--

34:06.070 --> 34:07.799
- WHATEVER, WHATEVER,
LET'S GO.

34:07.900 --> 34:10.698
I'M GONNA SUGAR CRASH.
- SERIOUSLY. UNBELIEVABLE.

34:10.800 --> 34:11.767
UNBELIEVABLE.

34:11.870 --> 34:13.906
WAIT, I--HOLD ON.

34:14.010 --> 34:15.659
I DIDN'T EVEN LOCK THE--
OH, GOD.

34:15.770 --> 34:18.045
- HERE WE GO.
YOU REALLY HAVE TO LOCK THAT?

34:18.150 --> 34:19.845
- WELL...

34:19.950 --> 34:21.679
- AMBER!
- YO.

34:21.780 --> 34:23.532
- HEY.
- HEY, WHAT'S UP?

34:23.640 --> 34:25.267
- LISTEN, I NEED YOU
TO PICK UP MAX FOR ME

34:25.370 --> 34:26.769
FROM SCHOOL AT 3:45, OKAY--
- NO, NO, NO.

34:26.890 --> 34:28.096
BUT YOU HAVE
TO BE THERE EARLY,

34:28.200 --> 34:29.360
SO YOU'RE THERE
WHEN HE COMES OUT--

34:29.480 --> 34:30.469
- UNCLE ADAM,
I CAN'T DO IT TODAY.

34:30.580 --> 34:32.309
- WHAT?
- I ALREADY TOLD CROSBY

34:32.410 --> 34:33.957
I'D HELP HIM IN HIS SESSION
WITH THE TRI-TONES TODAY,

34:34.070 --> 34:35.378
AND HE'S GONNA SHOW ME
STUFF ON THE BOARD--

34:35.480 --> 34:36.822
- YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO DO IT
ANOTHER DAY.

34:36.930 --> 34:40.104
I NEED YOU TO PICK UP MAX.
3:45. GET THERE EARLY.

34:43.080 --> 34:43.728
- CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

34:43.840 --> 34:47.662
- WHAT?

34:47.770 --> 34:51.115
- UM, I LOVE WORKING HERE.

34:51.220 --> 34:52.699
I LOVE IT, OKAY?
- OKAY.

34:52.810 --> 34:56.325
- UM, BUT I SORT OF FEEL
LIKE YOU'VE BEEN TREATING ME

34:56.430 --> 34:58.990
LIKE YOUR GIRL FRIDAY,
YOU KNOW?

34:59.090 --> 35:01.058
"DO THE DISHES,
AND CLEAN UP THE KITCHEN,

35:01.160 --> 35:03.435
AND, YOU KNOW,
DON'T SAY ANYTHING."

35:03.540 --> 35:06.782
I MEAN, I'M HAPPY TO HELP YOU
WITH WHATEVER YOU NEED,

35:06.890 --> 35:10.269
BUT I CAN REALLY BE
A VALUABLE ASSET HERE,

35:10.380 --> 35:14.828
AND I WANNA BE
A PART OF THE TEAM.

35:14.940 --> 35:16.510
AND I KINDA FEEL
LIKE YOU'VE BEEN

35:16.630 --> 35:21.556
BLOWING ME OFF
A LITTLE BIT LATELY.

35:21.670 --> 35:23.877
- CAN--CAN YOU SIT DOWN
FOR A SECOND?

35:28.290 --> 35:32.294
YOU'RE RIGHT, YOU'RE RIGHT,
ABOUT ALL OF IT.

35:41.550 --> 35:44.781
KRISTI NA--

35:44.900 --> 35:46.822
KRISTINA'S SICK.

35:50.000 --> 35:54.414
AND, UH, I'M...

35:54.530 --> 35:57.658
SORRY THAT I'VE BEEN ACTING
LIKE A JERK.

35:57.770 --> 35:59.419
I'M JUST DISTRACT ED,

35:59.530 --> 36:04.320
AND, UH, THAT'S
WHAT'S GOIN' ON.

36:05.920 --> 36:07.251
- I MEAN--

36:07.370 --> 36:09.600
WHAT DO YOU MEAN SICK?

36:09.710 --> 36:11.291
- I CAN'T GIVE YOU
ALL THE DETAILS.

36:11.410 --> 36:13.810
YOU'RE THE FIRST PERSON
I'M TELLING, SO...

36:16.340 --> 36:17.546
SORRY SOME OF THIS STUFF
IS GONNA FALL ON YOU,

36:17.650 --> 36:18.924
BUT I'M GONNA
KEEP ASKING YOU

36:19.030 --> 36:20.201
TO DO SOME
OF THESE THINGS FOR ME

36:20.310 --> 36:23.757
BECAUSE I'M GONNA NEED
YOUR HELP.

36:27.040 --> 36:29.452
- OKAY.
- ALL RIGHT.

36:35.500 --> 36:37.968
_ MAXI
[honking]

36:38.090 --> 36:39.569
MAX-A- ROONIE!

36:39.680 --> 36:40.942
HEY, DUDE.

36:41.060 --> 36:43.574
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
- I'M YOUR RIDE TODAY.

36:43.680 --> 36:45.739
- WELL, MOM USUALLY PICKS ME UP
AT SCHOOL.

36:45.850 --> 36:47.909
- I KNOW, BUT--
- SOMETIMES, IT'S MY DAD,

36:48.030 --> 36:50.237
BUT EVEN THAT'S RARE.
IT'S ALMOST ALWAYS MY MOM.

36:50.340 --> 36:51.614
- OKAY. WELL,
I'M YOUR RIDE TODAY,

36:51.720 --> 36:53.540
SO JUMP ON IN.
HERE WE GO.

36:53.650 --> 36:56.278
- WHERE IS MY MOM?
- WELL, SHE'S BUSY RIGHT NOW,

36:56.380 --> 36:58.826
BUT, UH, YOU'LL SEE HER
IN A LITTLE BIT, OKAY?

36:58.940 --> 37:01.135
- I HAD SOMETHING IMPORTANT
TO TALK TO HER ABOUT TODAY.

37:01.250 --> 37:02.478
- YOU DID?

37:02.590 --> 37:03.864
- YEAH.

37:03.980 --> 37:06.380
- WELL, I'M ALL EARS.

37:06.500 --> 37:08.218
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
WHAT DOES "ALL EARS" MEAN?

37:08.320 --> 37:10.948
- UM, JUST MEANS
I'M LISTENING.

37:11.050 --> 37:13.462
- COOL.

37:13.570 --> 37:15.845
ANYWAYS, YOU USED TO BE ABLE
TO BUY CANDY ANYTIME YOU WANT,

37:15.950 --> 37:17.463
NOT DURING CLASS, OBVIOUSLY,
BUT BEFORE SCHOOL,

37:17.580 --> 37:19.673
AFTER SCHOOL, RECESS.
- YEAH.

37:28.140 --> 37:30.995
- ZEEK.

37:31.110 --> 37:32.179
- HEY.
- HOW'D IT GO?

37:32.280 --> 37:34.726
- OH, WELL, IT WENT.

37:34.830 --> 37:36.388
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

37:36.490 --> 37:37.934
- WELL, THEY TOOK
TWO POINTS OFF

37:38.040 --> 37:42.659
'CAUSE I DIDN'T ADJUST
MY REARVIEW MIRROR.

37:42.770 --> 37:45.182
I ONLY GOT 98%.

37:45.290 --> 37:47.918
OH! GOTCHA.
- [chuckling] YOU--

37:48.020 --> 37:52.059
- HE SAID I HAD THE BEST
THREE-POINT TURN HE'D EVER SEEN.

37:52.160 --> 37:53.366
- WELL, I COULD'VE
TOLD HIM THAT.

37:53.470 --> 37:55.609
- MM.
- [chuckles]

38:02.070 --> 38:04.345
- HERE, THIS IS NOT HORRIBLE.

38:04.450 --> 38:05.997
- GREAT. THANK YOU SO MUCH.

38:06.110 --> 38:07.793
- THOUGHT THEY WOULD, LIKE,
GO CHINTZY ON THIS,

38:07.900 --> 38:09.822
BUT THEY DIDN'T.

38:11.840 --> 38:13.660
- ALL RIGHT,
THAT WAS OUR WEDDING.

38:13.770 --> 38:15.419
GOOD JOB.

38:15.530 --> 38:20.217
- IT WENT OKAY.
- YEAH, SEE?

38:20.330 --> 38:22.707
I'M PROUD OF YOU.
CONGRATULATIONS.

38:22.810 --> 38:24.630
- YEAH.
- ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU.

38:24.750 --> 38:26.706
- LOOK AT THE PEOPLE.
LOOK AT THEM, THE KIDS.

38:26.820 --> 38:28.742
THEY'RE SO HAPPY
WITH THEIR LITTLE WEDDING...

38:28.850 --> 38:30.909
- THEY ARE YOUR KIDS, RIGHT?
- SITUATION.

38:31.030 --> 38:33.089
SO YOUNG.
- THEY ARE YOUNG.

38:33.200 --> 38:34.303
- VERY YOUNG.

38:34.410 --> 38:36.162
- THEIR WHOLE LITTLE LIFE
AHEAD OF 'EM.

38:36.270 --> 38:37.441
- [laughs]

38:37.550 --> 38:39.689
YOU THINK THE WORLD'S
YOUR OYSTER?

38:39.800 --> 38:42.314
YOU'RE WRONG.

38:42.420 --> 38:44.695
- THAT'D BE HORRIBLE,
TO JUST THE END THE NIGHT,

38:44.800 --> 38:45.960
"LISTEN, HERE'S
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN..."

38:46.080 --> 38:47.798
- [chuckles]
- MM.

38:47.910 --> 38:49.832
- [moans] MEANWHILE, I WAS
PROBABLY YOUNGER THAN THAT

38:49.940 --> 38:52.113
WHEN I GOT MARRIED.

38:52.220 --> 38:55.701
- OH, YEAH, ME TOO.

38:55.810 --> 38:58.529
- OH, REALLY?

38:58.640 --> 39:02.189
OH. [clicks tongue]

39:02.300 --> 39:07.715
MAYBE THAT'S WHY YOU
DON'T LIKE WEDDINGS?

39:07.820 --> 39:09.447
- IT'S A FACTOR.

39:09.550 --> 39:11.825
- OKAY. FAIR ENOUGH.

39:11.930 --> 39:16.208
WELL, I THOUGHT
I WAS GONNA BE MARRIED FOREVER.

39:16.310 --> 39:18.130
- WELL, OF COURSE, THAT'S
HOW YOU ALWAYS THINK, RIGHT?

39:18.250 --> 39:21.595
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

39:21.700 --> 39:23.008
AND NOW, YOU'RE GONNA
DO IT AGAIN, RIGHT?

39:23.110 --> 39:24.668
- YEAH, BUT THIS
IS DIFFERENT.

39:24.770 --> 39:27.523
THIS TIME, I AM
GONNA BE MARRIED FOREVER.

39:31.540 --> 39:33.599
IT DOES HAPPEN, YOU KNOW?

39:33.710 --> 39:35.439
- YEAH.

39:35.540 --> 39:37.531
- IT MIGHT HAPPEN FOR THEM.
I HOPE IT DOES.

39:37.650 --> 39:39.026
I HOPE IT HAPPENS
FOR THEM.

39:39.130 --> 39:42.611
- HOW'S THE BRIDE?

39:42.720 --> 39:45.439
- ME TOO.

39:45.550 --> 39:48.519
HERE--HERE'S TO THEM.

39:48.620 --> 39:50.895
COME ON,
WE DID A WEDDING.

39:55.280 --> 39:57.840
[sighs]

39:57.940 --> 40:01.046
- OH, MY GOD, HONEY,
I GOTTA GET A NEW CD

40:01.150 --> 40:02.526
TO PUT NORA TO SLEEP.

40:02.640 --> 40:04.779
THOSE SONGS
ARE DRIVING ME NUTS.

40:06.470 --> 40:09.633
- HEY, ADAM.
- YEAH?

40:09.750 --> 40:13.789
- UM, CAN I TALK
TO YOU A SECOND?

40:13.890 --> 40:16.120
- YEAH, SURE.

40:16.240 --> 40:18.470
WHAT'S UP?

40:18.580 --> 40:20.616
- [exhales]

40:20.720 --> 40:23.371
I WANNA GO TO DR. BEDSLOE.

40:23.490 --> 40:25.344
- HONEY, REALLY?
THE GUY WHO MADE US WAIT

40:25.450 --> 40:26.929
FOR TWO HOURS,
AND THEN GAVE US TWO MINUTES

40:27.040 --> 40:29.861
OF INTERRUPTED CONVERSATION--
- I'VE DONE MY RESEARCH.

40:29.970 --> 40:32.666
I'VE CONSIDERED
ALL OF MY OPTIONS,

40:32.770 --> 40:34.761
AND I WANT DR. BEDSLOE
TO DO MY SURGERY.

40:34.880 --> 40:36.563
- HONEY, OBVIOUSLY,
IT'S YOUR CALL, OKAY?

40:36.670 --> 40:38.114
I JUST WANT YOU TO HAVE
THE BEST CARE POSSIBLE.

40:38.220 --> 40:39.391
I FEEL LIKE YOU SHOULD

40:39.500 --> 40:40.489
AT LEAST TALK TO DR. HARYANA--
- ADAM.

40:40.610 --> 40:43.602
- WHAT?
- I TRUST HIM.

40:43.710 --> 40:45.644
- OKAY. WELL, THEN,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

40:45.750 --> 40:46.978
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO.
IT'S LIKE DR. HARYANA SAID.

40:47.090 --> 40:48.910
IF YOU FEEL SOMETHING POSITIVE,
GO WITH IT.

40:49.030 --> 40:53.023
JUST, YOU GOTTA STAY POSITIVE--
- AND I'M SCARED.

40:53.140 --> 40:54.129
- OKAY, THAT'S OKAY
THAT YOU'RE SCARED.

40:54.240 --> 40:55.229
- PLEASE, STOP.
- WHAT?

40:55.340 --> 40:57.683
- ADAM.

40:57.800 --> 40:59.415
I KNOW THAT YOU'RE
TRYING TO MAKE

40:59.520 --> 41:02.933
EVERYTHING OKAY FOR ME.

41:03.040 --> 41:06.862
YOU ALWAYS HAVE
OUR WHOLE LIVES.

41:06.980 --> 41:09.210
AND I LOVE YOU SO MUCH
FOR THAT,

41:09.320 --> 41:14.189
BUT YOU HAVE
TO LET ME BE SCARED.

41:16.850 --> 41:19.227
I WANNA BE ABLE
TO COME TO YOU

41:19.330 --> 41:22.470
AND JUST SAY, "ADAM,
I'M--I'M REALLY SCARED TODAY,"

41:22.580 --> 41:23.979
AND I JUST WANT YOU
TO HEAR IT.

41:24.100 --> 41:26.022
I DON'T WANT YOU TO TELL ME
TO THINK POSITIVE

41:26.130 --> 41:32.137
OR TO--THAT EVERYTHING
IS GONNA BE GREAT,

41:32.240 --> 41:33.684
'CAUSE RIGHT NOW,
I'M NOT SURE

41:33.800 --> 41:37.725
THAT IT'S GOING TO BE.

41:37.840 --> 41:40.593
AND I JUST WANT TO BE ABLE

41:40.700 --> 41:42.975
TO FEEL SCARED.

41:43.080 --> 41:46.072
THAT'S JUST WHAT I NEED
FROM YOU RIGHT NOW.

41:49.290 --> 41:52.396
- OKAY.
I CAN DO THAT.

41:52.510 --> 41:54.978
- I LOVE YOU.
- I LOVE YOU TOO, SO MUCH.

41:55.090 --> 41:58.571
- [laughs]

41:58.680 --> 41:59.920
- KRISTINA, I'M SORRY.
I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU DOWN.

42:00.030 --> 42:02.134
- OH, HONEY--
- I'VE GOT NEWS!

42:02.240 --> 42:05.095
I'M RUNNING
FOR STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT.

42:05.210 --> 42:07.235
I'M GOING TO WIN.
I'M GOING TO GET ELECTED.

42:07.350 --> 42:08.442
I AM GOING TO GET
THE SCHOOL BOARD

42:08.560 --> 42:10.448
TO BRING BACK
THE VENDING MACHINE.

42:10.560 --> 42:12.482
- [laughs]
- ARE YOU EXCITED?

42:12.590 --> 42:13.318
